Ust-Kamenogorsk.title: Ust-Kamenogorsk
Ust-Kamenogorsk.byline: Ust-Kamenogorsk (Russian: Усть-Каменогорск, Kazakh: Өскемен, Oskemen) is a city in northeastern Kazakhstan dating to 1720, and is the capital of Eastern Kazakhstan Province, with a population of about 350,000 people.
